getGraphForSubgURL

public static void getGraphForSubgURL(ProxURL proxURL,
                                      edu.uci.ics.jung.graph.Graph graph)
In the subgraph table we don't store information about exactly which objects a particular link is connecting. For that information we query the database-wide link table. The problem is that the same objectID can appear more than once in a subgraph; if so, we cannot tell which instance of that objectID is to be connected by the given link.

We resolve this by showing the two (or more) instances of the objectID, and connecting all of them with multiple copies of the same link.

Parameters:
proxURL - subgraph URL to create the graph from
graph - Graph to fill with objects and links in the subgraph specified by subgURL. NB: cleared first!
